section.section:
"Common carrier" includes:
an airline company;
a car company, motor vehicle company, automobile company, or motor bus company;
a power boat company, vessel-boat company, steamboat company, or ferry company;
a railroad company, street railroad company, or sleeping car company;
a taxicab company;
a toll bridge company; and
a transit company.

"Common carrier" does not include:
a county revenue authority;
a toll bridge or other facility owned and operated by a county revenue authority;
a vanpool or launch service; or
a for-hire water carrier, as defined in § 8-744 of the Natural Resources Article.

text.section:
"Liquid-immersed distribution transformer" means a transformer that:
has an input voltage of 34,500 volts or less;
has an output voltage of 600 volts or less;
uses oil or other liquid as a coolant; and
is rated for operation at a frequency of 60 hertz.

"Renewable energy resource" means one or more of the following sources of energy, energy technology, or related credit:
solar;
wind;
tidal;
geothermal;
biomass, including waste-to-energy and landfill gas recovery;
hydroelectric facilities;
digester gas; and
a manufacturing or commercial waste-to-energy system or facility.
